From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 10 Dec 2025 19:53:03 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] firmware: cix: Add DSP IPC driver and SOF platform support
 for Sky1

Port CIX DSP mailbox driver and Sound Open Firmware (SOF) platform
support for Sky1 SoC.

CIX DSP IPC driver (drivers/firmware/cix/cix-dsp.c):
- Mailbox-based IPC abstraction for DSP communication
- Used by both remoteproc and SOF paths
- Exports cix_dsp_get_resource/cix_dsp_send_msg/cix_dsp_free interfaces

SOF Sky1 platform driver (sound/soc/sof/cix/):
- cix-common.c: Common CIX SOF platform code
- cix-sky1.c: Sky1-specific SOF platform driver
- Supports IPC3 protocol
- Memory regions: IRAM, DRAM, SRAM, mailbox
- Boot loader and firmware loading infrastructure

Note: SOF firmware (sof-sky1.ri) was never shipped by CIX/Radxa.
The driver loads but cannot bind without firmware. Current audio
path uses remoteproc DSP (cix,sky1-hifi5 compatible) which works
with dsp_fw.bin firmware.

API changes for mainline 6.18:
- MODULE_IMPORT_NS uses quoted strings
- SOF_IPC -> SOF_IPC_TYPE_3
- snd_sof_dsp_ops.remove returns void
